# Brain Studio — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development overrides;
# `.env.local` is ignored by git. Set the live values on Vercel
# under Project Settings → Environment Variables (Production +
# Preview + Development).
#
# These two NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars drive every URL the site renders:
# OG image footer, sitemap, robots, metadataBase, hreflang
# alternates, SiteHeader + SiteFooter "Source on GitHub" links.
# See `lib/urls.ts` for consumers.

# Public origin for the deployed site.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://thebrainstudio.org

# Source repository URL surfaced in SiteHeader + SiteFooter
# GitHub icons and About-page affordances.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GITHUB_URL=https://github.com/thebrainstudio/web

# --- Backend (Vercel-only; never committed) ---
# Set in Vercel Project Settings → Environment Variables.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TRIBE_API_BASE=<your Mirror API base>
# HF_TOKEN=<your HuggingFace token, if Mirror falls back to HF>
